The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Nov. 21: Cairn India has been forced to cap oil production from its Rajasthan fields with both ONGC and the directorate general of hydrocarbons delaying in giving their approval to its plans for raising the output by 20 per cent. Cairn India produces 125,000 barrels of crude per day from the Mangala oilfield, the largest among the 15 discoveries in the Rajasthan block RJ-ON-90/1.                             
	 New Delhi, Nov. 21: Hindustan Copper Ltd (HCL) will more than double the capacity of its Madhya Pradesh mine to 5 million tonnes before its 4,000-crore follow-on public offer, which is likely this month. Hindustan Copper proposes to engage contractors for the development of the Malanjkhand underground mine for a production capacity of 5 million tonnes per annum, the company said.                            
	 New Delhi, Nov. 21: The commerce ministry has put on hold a decision           
	 relaxing SEZ rules relating to land contiguity, as requested by Vedanta Group and Raheja Developers, after the revenue department raised concerns over tax evasion.                            
	 New Delhi, Nov. 21: The Indian Sugar Mills Association has said the government should fix the final price of ethanol at the earliest for the smooth implementation of five per cent ethanol blending with petrol.                            
	 New Delhi, Nov. 21: Micro finance institutions (MFI) have asked the Reserve Bank to direct banks to set up an emergency fund of Rs 1,000 crore to help them tide over slowdown in their business.                                                                                                                          
